When I was a child I dreamed of being the best climber in the World. It was a crazy, wild ride to get there and now I’m training for the Olympic Games! I can’t believe the journey I have had so far and I still feel like I have so much more to give. My love for this sport just continues to grow. I can’t wait to speak at @kendalmountainfestival on Saturday 17th November and share some tales and insights into my career so far.
Link in bio for talk tickets. .
#talk #climbing

Do you love JUMPING? I do. ☺️ And I really wanna be able to jump around again!!! It’s funny how just a couple of moves can make you so happy. This one took a lot of attempts to get the timing and distance. Hopefully not too much longer before my finger is ready for some jumps ☺️ #throwback #thursday #rehab #comebackstronger #jump

Happy face because my finger is on the mend. I had another scan today to check on the progress. It’s so good to actually see the improvements I have been feeling ☺️ It’s definitely not over yet but I’m happy! 📷 @Owenmadeup
.
. #happy #comebackstronger #climbing

Today was a fun day! Myself and @leahcraneclimbing ran workshops at the @youthclimbingsymposium ! We put loads of volumes and funky holds, made up lots of silly challenges, jumped around and laughed a lot! There were some super psyched young people who tried hard and really got involved! Creativity is one of the key elements to keeping climbing and training fun! We get to do it all again tomorrow! .
.

Woke up, ate breakfast, jumped in the pool, went for coffee, swam in the sea, lay in the sun, went for juice and pizza, watched the lead World Cup Final (congrats to @steghiso & @allezjain for their insane performances), read my book in the sun, then I did some WCS work and now it’s time for dinner and a glass of red. Today’s been simple, sweet and blissful! .
@leahcraneclimbing 📷 #holiday #break #pool #happy
